<%# Phase 9 (requirement.md §5.15) — LiveDashboard.broadcast_event_stats replaces this exact node
    (Turbo::StreamsChannel.broadcast_replace_to target: "live-stats-#{event.id}") on every
    check-in/registration write; admin/scan_events/index.html.erb also renders it directly for
    first paint before any broadcast has happened.

    Every value below comes from Event's own #checked_in_participant_count/
    #arrived_today_participant_count/#currently_in_venue_count (app/models/event.rb) — real,
    distinct-participant counts, not EventLiveStats' cumulative scan counters. See those methods'
    own comment for why: this dashboard isn't the high-frequency check-in-desk write path
    EventLiveStats exists to serve cheaply (Admin::EventsController#show's own precedent), and a
    "N checked in" sitting next to "M registered" reads as a headcount, not a raw scan tally.

    Locals: event (Event). %>
<div id="live-stats-<%= event.id %>">
  <div class="row g-3">
    <div class="col-md-6 col-xl-3">
      <%= render "shared/stat_widget", label: "Registered", value: event.participants.count, icon: "bx-user-plus", color: "primary" %>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-6 col-xl-3">
      <%= render "shared/stat_widget", label: "Checked In", value: event.checked_in_participant_count, icon: "bx-log-in-circle", color: "success" %>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-6 col-xl-3">
      <%= render "shared/stat_widget", label: "Arrived Today", value: event.arrived_today_participant_count, icon: "bx-calendar-check", color: "info" %>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-6 col-xl-3">
      <%= render "shared/stat_widget", label: "Currently In Venue", value: event.currently_in_venue_count, icon: "bx-walk", color: "warning" %>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="row g-3 mt-0">
    <div class="col-12">
      <div class="card mb-0">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h6 class="font-size-15 text-muted mb-2">Check-in velocity</h6>
          <%# Explicit full path, not a bare "sparkline" relative lookup — this partial is also
              rendered via Turbo::StreamsChannel.broadcast_replace_to (LiveDashboard), whose
              ActionController::Renderer context doesn't carry the same admin/scan_events prefix a
              normal request-rendered view gets, so a relative lookup 404s there even though it
              works fine from index.html.erb. %>
          <%= render "admin/scan_events/sparkline", series: LiveMetricBucket.sparkline_series(event: event, metric: :check_in) %>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
